<!-- Clarification about ownership of work done during the Engagement Term -->
<a_left_sidehead>Ownership of Work</a_left_sidehead>
  <numbered_2_para>The Contractor accepts that, to the fullest extent permissible under Applicable Law --- save where otherwise agreed to in writing by the Company --- Work, including any and all materials prepared by the Contractor under this Contract shall be considered proprietary to the Company.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para xname="Take Action">Where any Work or Rights are not deemed proprietary to the Company under Applicable Law, the Contractor hereby assigns to the Company all of its Right, title, interest in and to Work (and any other Rights relating thereto). The Contractor shall also without compensation and forthwith upon demand, whether during the Engagement Term or otherwise, execute and deliver to the Company any applications, specifications, oaths, assignments, recordations, or any instruments of transfer, and take such action as may be requested by the Company, to secure and ensure protection of such of the Company's rights and interest and to effect the transfer of such Rights, title, and/or interests to the Company.</numbered_2_para>
    <numbered_3_para>Actions under Clause <xref to="Take Action" /> include the signing of documents and giving of testimony required in the course of the Company applying for or maintaining any Rights, or in the course of any litigation or other legal proceeding related to Work (and any Rights relating thereto) anywhere in the world.</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>The Contractor's obligation to execute or cause to be executed any such instrument, papers, or take any action described under this Clause <xref to="Take Action"/> shall continue after the termination of this Contract until the expiration of the last of such Rights in any country in the world.</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para xname="license">If, under Applicable Law, the Contractor is unable to assign all or any part of such Rights to the Company, or if approval of such assignment is required from a government authority and such approval is not granted, the Contractor hereby licenses to the Company such Rights as cannot be assigned, so that the Company shall have the complete right to use and right to exploit the applicable Work (and any Rights relating thereto), and any modified or derivative works thereof. Unless otherwise agreed between the Parties in writing, the license described under this Clause <xref to="license" /> shall be perpetual, free of charge, sub-licensable, irrevocable, exclusive (excluding both the Contractor and all third parties), worldwide, and transferable.</numbered_3_para>
