  <numbered_2_para>The Contractor hereby irrevocably designates and appoints the Company (including its duly authorized officers and agents, as may be relevant or required) as zir agent and attorney in fact, but only to the extent where the Company is unable - because of the Contractor's mental or physical incapacity or unavailability - to secure the Contractor's signature to apply for or to pursue any rights or interest protecting application covering the Rights or Works under this Contract, to act for and on zir behalf and stead to execute and file any such applications, and to do all other lawfully permitted acts to further the application for, prosecution, issuance, maintenance or transfer of such rights or interest with the same legal force and effect as if personally executed by the Contractor.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>The Contractor further agrees not to exercise any rights or interests in Rights and/or Works that under Applicable Law cannot be assigned or licensed to the Company pursuant to the foregoing, including but not limited to right to claim authorship and the right not to suffer false attribution of authorship, except with the prior written consent of the Company.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>At any time (whether during the Engagement Term or after), where the Contractor intends to integrate and/or incorporate any of zir proprietary rights and/or previous work in furtherance of zir provision and/or performance of the Services and fulfilment zir obligations under this Contract, such intention shall be communicated in writing to the Company prior to any such intended integration and/or incorporation. Where the Company, at its sole and absolute discretion consents to such integration and/or incorporation, the Contractor hereby grants to the Company an exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free, perpetual, irrevocable license to use, distribute, modify, publish, sub-license, and/or otherwise exploit such integration and/or incorporation in connection with the Business of the Company.</numbered_2_para>

