  <a_left_sidehead>Dealing with Confidential Information and Work</a_left_sidehead>
  <numbered_2_para>The Company does not give any warranty or representation to the Contractor as to the accuracy or completeness of Confidential Information, and the Company shall not be liable for any damages, claims, or losses resulting from the use of Confidential Information.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>The Contractor hereby undertakes that during the Engagement Term and after, ze shall protect Work and Confidential Information using at least the same standard of care ze applies to zir own proprietary and/or confidential Information (but no less than reasonable care), and to the extent not prohibited by Applicable Law, ensure that Confidential Information and Work which ze accesses, create, amends, or otherwise deals with, is stored, handled, and maintained in such a way as to prevent unauthorised access or disclosure.</numbered_2_para>
<numbered_2_para>Save where expressly permitted under this Contract or required for the Contractor's provision and/or performance of the Services or zir fulfilment of zir obligations under this Contract, the Contractor shall not copy, reproduce, adapt, modify, translate, manufacture, market, publish, distribute, sell, license (or sublicense), transfer, rent, lease, transmit, broadcast, display, use, or otherwise exploit (i) any Work or Confidential Information; or (ii) disclose any or Work or Confidential Information to any person.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>Nothing in this Contract, whether by implication or otherwise, and whether directly or indirectly, shall or be construed as granting to or conferring upon Contractor any Rights (whether to Work, Confidential Information, or otherwise).</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>The Contractor hereby acknowledges and accepts that Work and Confidential Information, and all Rights therein, are and shall remain the sole and exclusive property of the Company.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>Save where expressly permitted under this Contract or otherwise agreed to by the Company in writing, the Contractor hereby undertakes to:-</numbered_2_para>
    <numbered_3_para>hold in strictest confidence the Confidential Information;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>take all steps (including any steps that the Company may direct or suggest) to prevent any unauthorised reproduction, duplication, use, access, or modification of Confidential Information and Work by any person;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>take all steps (including any steps that the Company may direct or suggest) to ensure that documents and/or items of work-in-progress that embody Work or Confidential Information are kept and maintained securely (including, using disk encryption and two-factor authentication protection whenever such options are available);</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>not create derivative works from, provide access electronically to, or enter into computer memory beyond the Company's control, Work or Confidential Information (including any portion or copy thereof) in any form; and </numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>not apply for, or apply to register, any Rights in or related to Confidential Information or Work, in Singapore or any other country or region.</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_2_para>For the avoidance of doubt, Confidential Information shall not include any information or data which:-</numbered_2_para>
    <numbered_3_para>at the date of its disclosure can be proved by documentary evidence to be Information which is publicly available or which subsequently becomes publicly available, unless such public available is due to or relating to the Contractor's breach of this Contract or a third party's breach of any confidentiality obligations; or</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>at the date of its disclosure can be proved by documentary evidence to be already rightfully available and/or in the possession of the Contractor prior to the Contractor's receipt of the same from the Company, and that the same had not been acquired (whether directly or indirectly) from the Company or any person known to the Contractor as being under an obligation of confidence; or</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>is compelled to be disclosed by Applicable Law of a competent jurisdiction to which the Contractor is subject, or by a court of competent jurisdiction, regulator, or any competent supervisory or regulatory body to which the Contractor may be subject, provide that where the Contractor is so compelled, ze shall prior to making any disclosure and save where prohibited under Applicable Law, promptly inform the Company and take the Company's instructions as to the form, nature, content, and extent of any proposed disclosure; or</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>is developed by the Contractor independently without the use and/or reference to Confidential Information.</numbered_3_para>

